gameframework.motion.blocking

Interface MoveBlockerRulesApplier

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MoveBlockerRulesApplierDefaultImpl

    public interface MoveBlockerRulesApplier
    The classes implementing this interface are used to apply movement rules to a movable. To move, a movable must not be blocked by a MoveBlocker. It's this interface role to provide a way to check if this is occuring.

    • Method Detail

      • moveValidationProcessing

        boolean moveValidationProcessing(GameMovable m,
                                 java.util.Vector<MoveBlocker> obs)
        This method checks if the movable can move according to the moveblockers in obs. If true, this means that no MoveBlocker blocks the way of the GameMovable.
        Parameters:
        m - the movable to test
        obs - the MoveBlocker vector
        Returns:
        true if the movable is allowed to move, false otherwise
